The paper focuses on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their application in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of lifelong learning, which falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the organization of incoming data into feature-driven super-classes, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
